The Board shall consist of the following members:
One member of the Senate of Maryland, appointed by the President of the Senate;
One member of the House of Delegates, appointed by the Speaker of the House;
The Secretary of Human Resources, or the Secretary's designee;
The Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene, or the Secretary's designee;
The Secretary of Information Technology, or the Secretary's designee;
The Secretary of Aging, or the Secretary's designee;
A representative of the Office of Homeland Security, appointed by the Governor;
A representative of 2-1-1 Maryland, Inc., appointed by the Board of Directors of 2-1-1 Maryland;
A representative of each 2-1-1 Maryland call center, appointed by the call center;
A representative of the Maryland Child Care Resource Network, appointed by the Governor;
A representative of the Maryland State Association of United Ways, appointed by the Governor; and
Two members of the public with experience in telecommunications, appointed by the Governor.
